<item>
            <title>[DERBY-3784] ImportExportTest doesn&apos;t detect lack of expected errors</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DERBY-3784</link>
                <project id="10594" key="DERBY">Derby</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;I observed that ImportExportTest contains many test cases which do try/catch/assertSQLException, but none of them call fail() at the end of the try block. Example:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;	public void testEarlyEndOfFile() throws Exception {&lt;br/&gt;
		Connection c = getConnection();&lt;br/&gt;
		try &lt;/p&gt;
{
			doImportFromFile(c, &quot;extin/EndOfFile.txt&quot; , &quot;T4&quot; , null , null , null, 0);
		}
&lt;p&gt; catch (SQLException e) &lt;/p&gt;
{
			assertSQLState(&quot;XIE0E&quot;, e);
		}
&lt;p&gt;	}&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I think this means that if the expected exception isn&apos;t thrown the test still passes.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
